# ============================================================
# ITEM CORE ARCHITECTURE
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: architecture
domain: item
scope: item.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines the canonical architectural role of item in CivilizationOS.

## design_intent
Item is the bounded identifiable object unit
that may be possessed,
placed,
used,
transferred,
consumed,
or referenced
under explicit scope.

Item is not identical to inventory.
Item is the identifiable object meaning;
inventory is one of the systems that tracks its possession state.

## architectural_position
Item sits between:
- asset/object identity
- inventory tracking
- housing placement
- market/trade exposure
- work/quest consumption or usage

## required_behavior
- item identity must remain explicit
- current and historical item states must remain distinguishable
- possession and placement meaning must remain explicit
- use/transfer/consumption meaning must remain explicit

## canonical_rules
- item identity must not be replaced by listing or placement projection
- possession does not imply unrestricted transfer authority
- historical item trace must remain queryable
- ambiguous item ownership or usage fails closed

## state_model
The item domain distinguishes:
- registered item
- possessed item
- placed item
- restricted item
- consumed/retired item
- historical item

## actor_boundary
- item owner/holder
- operator
- reviewer
- adapter

## decision_matrix
- if item identity is unclear, stop item-sensitive action
- if possession basis is unclear, fail closed
- if transfer/use exceeds authority, deny
- if item becomes historical, preserve trace

## review_checklist
- item identity is explicit
- possession/placement/use meanings are explicit
- historical distinction is explicit
